In Linux systems, the command to view all folders is usually 'ls'. If you want to display only folders rather than files, you can use the' ls - d */'command. This operation needs to be completed in the opened terminal.
According to the screen image you provided, the terminal has been opened, so we should enter the command 'ls - d */'. The following is the JSON format for executing this action:```json
[
    {"action_type": "KeyboardAction", "keyboard_action_type": "text", "keyboard_text": "ls -d */"}
]
```
